{"type":"text","timestamp":1773481815233,"sessionID":"ses_314408b3affedlAR2t7y2tf3to","part":{"id":"prt_cebc0cdb9001hq5fTPVOrNcF5C","sessionID":"ses_314408b3affedlAR2t7y2tf3to","messageID":"msg_cebc0c672001LAlQTeN0xMXhum","type":"text","text":"All tasks complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Implementation Summary\n\n**File created:** `src/lib/wishlist-store.ts`\n\n### WishlistItem Type\n```typescript\ninterface WishlistItem {\n  id: string;        // UUID v4\n  text: string;      // Description\n  created_at: string; // ISO 8601 timestamp\n  tags: string[];    // Optional categorization tags\n}\n```\n\n### Storage\n- **Location:** `.wombo-combo/wishlist.yml`\n- **Format:** Flat YAML array of WishlistItem objects\n- Uses atomic writes (write to `.tmp` then rename) following the existing codebase pattern\n\n### CRUD Functions\n1. **`loadWishlist(projectRoot)`** — Loads all items from the YAML file, returns `[]` if file doesn't exist or is empty, normalizes items to ensure all fields are present\n2. **`addItem(projectRoot, text, tags?)`** — Creates a new item with auto-generated UUID and current timestamp, appends to the array, saves, returns the new item\n3. **`deleteItem(projectRoot, id)`** — Finds and removes an item by ID, returns `true` if found/removed, `false` otherwise\n4. **`listItems(projectRoot)`** — Convenience alias for `loadWishlist()`\n\n### Design Decisions\n- Followed the `quest-store.ts` pattern (simpler, self-contained) rather than the heavier `task-store.ts` pattern (which has meta files, migration, validation schemas)\n- Used `node:crypto.randomUUID()` for ID generation\n- Used the existing `yaml` (v2) library already in the project\n- Used atomic writes via tmp file + rename for crash safety\n- No new dependencies added","time":{"start":1773481815232,"end":1773481815232}}}
